            <section xml:id="operations_session_duration">
                <title>Session Duration</title>
                <para role="definiton" xml:id="def_sessionDuration"> A <xref linkend="term_session"/> begins after a
                    successful <xref linkend="op_logOn"/> operation. The session ends after the
                    <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> has invoked the <xref linkend="op_logOff"/> operation, or it may
                    be terminated by the <xref linkend="term_service"/>.</para>

                <para>This specification does not define any behaviors regarding Service termination
                    of Sessions; time out intervals, reasons for forced termination, and related
                    aspects are all implementation defined.</para>

                <para>A Session may cover multiple HTTP connections. Since transferring and
                    rendering of content may be very timeconsuming, Sessions should be kept open for
                    as long as possible, in order to minimize the risk for a negative User
                    experience.</para>
            </section>

            <section xml:id="operations_session_initializationSequence">
                <title>Session Initialization Sequence</title>

                <para role="definition" xml:id="def_sessionInitializationSequence"
                    xreflabel="Session Initialization Sequence"> To ensure interoperability and
                    consistent behavior between implementations, Reading Systems must invoke the
                    below operations in the given sequence at the onset of every Session, and before
                    invoking any other protocol operation. <orderedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>The <xref linkend="op_logOn"/> operation, with a return value of
                                    <varname>true</varname> (<xref linkend="bib_xsdDatatypes"/>)
                            </para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para> The <xref linkend="op_getServiceAttributes"/> operation</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para> The <xref linkend="op_setReadingSystemAttributes"/> operation,
                                with a return value of <varname>true</varname> (<xref
                                    linkend="bib_xsdDatatypes"/>) </para>
                        </listitem>
                    </orderedlist>
                </para>

                <para>If a Service throws a <link linkend="apiReferenceFaults">Fault</link> during
                    the <token>Session Initialization Sequence</token> phase, or if the above
                    specified return values or not given, then the session remains uninitialized and
                    must be either be reinitialized, or the attempt to log the Reading System on to
                    the Service must be aborted.</para>

                <para>All operations defined by this specification except the <xref
                        linkend="op_logOn"/> operation are valid to invoke after the <token>Session
                        Initialization Sequence</token> has been completed.</para>

                <para>A Service must throw a <xref linkend="ft_InvalidOperationFault"/> if a Reading
                    System does not honor the above initialization sequence.</para>
            </section>

