             <section xml:id="operations_content_issuing_pdtb">
                <title>Rights management</title>
                 <para>A Service may provide all or parts of its content collection in protected form. This version
                 of this specification allows the <xref linkend="bib_pdtb2"/> format to be used for content
                 protection.</para>            
                 <para><remark role="todo">TODO discuss interop issues: Neither Reading Systems nor Services are required
                 to support the PTDB2 format. How is the support communicated at initializationtime (*attributes); what will happen in 
                 case of mismatch</remark></para>   
                <para><remark role="todo">TODO give examples of PTDB2 contentMetadata etc for encrypted books</remark></para>                
                <para><remark role="todo">TODO give example of or at least discuss using only rights expression language but no encryption</remark></para>
                 
                     <para>If <xref linkend="term_content"/> is protected using <xref linkend="bib_pdtb2"/>, then there will be a metadata item in the <link linkend="tp_contentMetadata">contentMetadata</link> named "pdtb2:specVersion" with a value of "2005-1" and there will be resources with mimeTypes beginning with "application/x-pdtb".  The <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> can access these resources even if it does not support <xref linkend="bib_pdtb2"/>, but it might not be able to decrypt all the <xref linkend="term_content"/>.</para>
                     <para>If some <xref linkend="term_content"/> has an Authorization Object (<abbrev>AO</abbrev>), the <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> can inspect it for the name of the key that secures the key to decrypt the <xref linkend="term_content"/>.</para>
                     <para>The <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> may call <link linkend="op_getKeyExchangeObject">getKeyExchangeObject</link> with an <link linkend="tp_itemList">itemList</link> of names of keys on its keyring (these can be all or some of the symmetric keys or public/private keypairs the <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> supports) and the name of the requested key.  The <xref linkend="term_service"/> is free to choose any of the keys in the supportedPublicKeyNames to encrypt the Key Exchange Object (<abbrev>KXO</abbrev>).  If the <xref linkend="term_service"/> does not have any of those keys or if the <xref linkend="term_user"/> is not authorized to access the <xref linkend="term_content"/>, then the <xref linkend="term_service"/> will instead reply with an <link linkend="ft_InvalidOperationFault">InvalidOperationFault</link>.  The <xref linkend="term_service"/> is responsible for keeping a list of authorized key names.</para>
                     <para>For example, a <xref linkend="term_user"/> wants to read an encrypted <abbrev>PDTB</abbrev> from the Zenith Library.  The <abbrev>AO</abbrev> is itself encrypted with a key named "DAISY.gy-zlog.afc26219-auth":</para>
                     <programlisting><xi:include href="./samples/authorization.xml" parse="text"></xi:include></programlisting>
                     <para>The <xref linkend="term_user"/> has keys for the <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> (an Acme Reader Express) as well as user account keys supplied by Haute-Bibliothèque and Apex Talking Books, Inc.  The <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> calls the <link linkend="op_getKeyExchangeObject">getKeyExchangeObject</link> operation with first parameter (supportedPublicKeyNames) as:</para>
                     <programlisting>
                         &lt;itemList&gt;
                         &lt;!-- The vendor, model and instance keys of the reading system. --&gt;
                         &lt;item&gt;DAISY.lv-acme&lt;/item&gt;
                         &lt;item&gt;DAISY.lv-acme.ReaderExpress&lt;/item&gt;
                         &lt;item&gt;DAISY.lv-acme.0034218&lt;/item&gt;
                         &lt;!-- User account keys granted by Haute-Bibliothèque and Apex. --&gt;
                         &lt;item&gt;DAISY.ca-qqhb.006442&lt;/item&gt;
                         &lt;item&gt;DAISY.au-atbi.userKey-4C452DB4&lt;/item&gt;
                         &lt;/itemList&gt;
                     </programlisting>
                     <para>and the second parameter (requestedKeyName) as "DAISY.gy-zlog.afc26219-auth".</para>
                     <para>The <xref linkend="term_service"/> determines that the <xref linkend="term_user"/> is authorized to receive this key.  The <xref linkend="term_serviceProvider"/> have determined that the Acme Reader Express is a trusted <xref linkend="term_readingSystem"/> model, so the <xref linkend="term_service"/> returns a <abbrev>KXO</abbrev> encrypted with the model key, "DAISY.lv-acme.ReaderExpress":</para>
                     <programlisting><xi:include href="./samples/kxo.xml" parse="text"></xi:include></programlisting>
                 
             </section>
        </section>

